.Sh "\s-1POSIX::\s0SigAction"
.IX Subsection "\s-1POSIX::\s0SigAction"
.Ip "new" 8
.IX Item "new"
Creates a new \f(CWPOSIX::SigAction\fR object which corresponds to the C
\f(CWstruct sigaction\fR.  This object will be destroyed automatically when it is
no longer needed.  The first parameter is the fully-qualified name of a sub
which is a signal-handler.  The second parameter is a \f(CWPOSIX::SigSet\fR
object, it defaults to the empty set.  The third parameter contains the
\f(CWsa_flags\fR, it defaults to 0.
.Sp
.Vb 2
\&        $sigset = POSIX::SigSet->new(SIGINT, SIGQUIT);
\&        $sigaction = POSIX::SigAction->new( 'main::handler', $sigset, &POSIX::SA_NOCLDSTOP );
.Ve
This \f(CWPOSIX::SigAction\fR object should be used with the \f(CWPOSIX::sigaction()\fR
function.
